- Yeah.
- And Lily Tuber is really bossy.

1249
00:59:53,507 --> 00:59:54,508
Uh-huh.

1250
00:59:55,676 --> 00:59:59,430
Getting divorced with a kid can be
one of the hardest things you'll ever do.

1251
01:00:01,098 --> 01:00:02,980
It's like a death without a body.

1252
01:00:05,144 --> 01:00:08,437
I know personally.
I've been there four different times.

1253
01:00:08,522 --> 01:00:10,144
You've been divorced four times?

1254
01:00:10,233 --> 01:00:11,354
Married four times.

1255
01:00:11,775 --> 01:00:12,936
Three divorces.

1256
01:00:13,986 --> 01:00:16,319
This last one will stick, God willing.

1257
01:00:16,405 --> 01:00:18,787
That's why I graduated into family law,

1258
01:00:19,074 --> 01:00:21,327
to help people survive this painful time.

1259
01:00:23,078 --> 01:00:24,290
Here's how I see it.

1260
01:00:25,706 --> 01:00:28,669
If we get bogged down
in "who did this," and "who did that,"

1261
01:00:28,751 --> 01:00:30,433
and "I don't want to pay the two dollars,"

1262
01:00:30,461 --> 01:00:33,134
it'll just cost you more money
and time and...

1263
01:00:34,173 --> 01:00:35,264
emotional stress,

1264
01:00:35,341 --> 01:00:37,763
and you'll probably end up
with the same result anyway.

1265
01:00:37,843 --> 01:00:38,844
Right.

1266
01:00:39,094 --> 01:00:41,967
I mean, I agree with that philosophy.
She does too, I'm sure.

1267
01:00:42,055 --> 01:00:45,138
And I always go with the truth,
no matter where that takes us.

1268
01:00:45,476 --> 01:00:47,598
You know, most people in my business
make up the truth

1269
01:00:47,645 --> 01:00:49,167
so they can get where they need to go.

1270
01:00:49,688 --> 01:00:51,820
You're just transactions to them.

1271
01:00:51,899 --> 01:00:53,781
I-I like to think of you as people.

1272
01:00:53,859 --> 01:00:55,651
Oh, okay, good.

1273
01:00:55,736 --> 01:00:57,198
And not just you, her too.

1274
01:00:57,280 --> 01:00:58,110
Yes.

1275
01:00:58,197 --> 01:01:00,329
You know, this can be
a really ugly process.

1276
01:01:00,408 --> 01:01:03,080
But I also believe
it doesn't have to be terrible.

1277
01:01:03,369 --> 01:01:04,740
I'm glad to hear you say that.

1278
01:01:05,288 --> 01:01:06,289
Um...

1279
01:01:06,872 --> 01:01:09,245
I'd love to keep expenses down
as much as possible.

1280
01:01:09,333 --> 01:01:10,334
Of course you do.

1281
01:01:10,918 --> 01:01:14,922
I charge 450 an hour
and I need a $10,000 retainer to start.

1282
01:01:15,923 --> 01:01:18,636
I'll see if I can get an advance
on the Broadway transfer.

1283
01:01:18,717 --> 01:01:21,470
And keep in mind,
you'll have to pay for her lawyer.

1284
01:01:21,554 --> 01:01:23,005
Oh. I didn't...

1285
01:01:25,558 --> 01:01:27,470
- What?
- Well, at least part of her.

1286
01:01:27,560 --> 01:01:29,141
It doesn't make sense, does it?

1287
01:01:29,520 --> 01:01:32,573
I mean, you're doing this
because you love your kid.

1288
01:01:33,232 --> 01:01:36,525
And in doing so, you're draining money
from your kid's education.

1289
01:01:36,610 --> 01:01:38,572
- It seems ridiculous.
- Oh, it is.

1290
01:01:38,737 --> 01:01:39,988
It is, boy.

1291
01:01:41,574 --> 01:01:43,366
We'll have to respond right away.

1292
01:01:44,993 --> 01:01:46,665
Your son goes to school out here?

1293
01:01:46,745 --> 01:01:48,997
Yeah, temporarily. We agreed.

1294
01:01:49,457 --> 01:01:52,039
Her pilot went to series
and I wanted to accommodate her,

1295
01:01:52,125 --> 01:01:54,248
as she's often felt
we do things on my terms.

1296
01:01:54,337 --> 01:01:56,589
Be a better husband in divorce.

1297
01:01:56,922 --> 01:01:59,595
I guess something like that,
but we live in New York.

1298
01:02:00,718 --> 01:02:02,600
Well, with your kid
going to school out here,

1299
01:02:02,678 --> 01:02:04,139
the court may see it differently.

1300
01:02:04,221 --> 01:02:05,263
Will we go to court?

1301
01:02:05,348 --> 01:02:07,350
No, no, we don't want to go to court.

1302
01:02:07,725 --> 01:02:09,517
The courts in California are a disaster.

1303
01:02:09,602 --> 01:02:11,644
No, that's just how
we have to think about it.

1304
01:02:12,145 --> 01:02:13,897
I'm not sure these are my glasses.

1305
01:02:14,273 --> 01:02:15,984
Where are you living while you're here?

1306
01:02:16,066 --> 01:02:17,368
I'm in a hotel right now.

1307
01:02:17,443 --> 01:02:18,654
No, a hotel doesn't look good.

1308
01:02:18,736 --> 01:02:20,197
- To who?
- The court.

1309
01:02:20,279 --> 01:02:22,200
You just said
we weren't going to go to court.

1310
01:02:22,281 --> 01:02:23,562
No, of course, of course.

1311
01:02:23,616 --> 01:02:26,118
We have to prepare to go to court,
hoping we don't go to court.

1312
01:02:26,201 --> 01:02:27,202
Okay.

1313
01:02:27,536 --> 01:02:28,997
You should get a place in LA.

1314
01:02:29,538 --> 01:02:32,170
And get a place near her.
It looks better for custody reasons.

1315
01:02:32,249 --> 01:02:34,542
She's in West Hollywood.
That'll be expensive.

1316
01:02:34,627 --> 01:02:36,539
I-I guess I could rent
our New York apartment.

1317
01:02:36,629 --> 01:02:37,630
Don't rent it.

1318
01:02:37,963 --> 01:02:40,215
You have to continue to prove
New York residence.

1319
01:02:40,299 --> 01:02:42,431
And of course, if you have a place in LA,

1320
01:02:42,510 --> 01:02:44,892
it's hard to show you all live
in New York, isn't it?

1321
01:02:44,970 --> 01:02:45,971
So...

1322
01:02:46,889 --> 01:02:48,010
what do I do?

1323
01:02:48,140 --> 01:02:51,474
I recommend you spend
as much time as you can with your son.

1324
01:02:52,395 --> 01:02:54,347
Many people fight for that time,

1325
01:02:54,438 --> 01:02:55,849
then they don't even use it.

1326
01:02:56,399 --> 01:02:57,600
They just want to win.

1327
01:02:57,858 --> 01:03:00,411
This shouldn't be
that complicated, right?

1328
01:03:00,486 --> 01:03:02,107
I mean, we're a New York family.

1329
01:03:02,363 --> 01:03:04,865
I think it's all
pretty straightforward. Right?

1330
01:03:04,948 --> 01:03:06,990
I hope so, yes.

1331
01:03:07,910 --> 01:03:09,362
I see no reason...

1332
01:03:10,120 --> 01:03:12,252
You both love your child.

1333
01:03:13,248 --> 01:03:14,420
You respect each other.

1334
01:03:14,750 --> 01:03:16,922
Why this shouldn't be
relatively pain-free.

1335
01:03:17,002 --> 01:03:18,083
Right.

1336
01:03:18,170 --> 01:03:20,082
I think you have my glasses.

1337
01:03:22,550 --> 01:03:23,761
That makes sense.

1338
01:03:24,760 --> 01:03:27,473
- What have you been doing?
- Reading this magazine.

1339
01:03:27,555 --> 01:03:29,517
You were reading California Lawyer?

1340
01:03:29,598 --> 01:03:30,439
Yeah.

1341
01:03:30,516 --> 01:03:33,188
Okay, I'm almost done.

1342
01:03:33,602 --> 01:03:35,694
I wouldn't expect too much from that cat.

1343
01:03:37,856 --> 01:03:40,489
- What kind of pet do you want?
- I don't know...

1344
01:03:40,568 --> 01:03:43,320
I want you to know
that eventually this will all be over,

1345
01:03:43,404 --> 01:03:45,205
and whatever we win or lose...

1346
01:03:45,781 --> 01:03:48,704
it'll be the two of you
having to figure this out together.

1347
01:03:49,410 --> 01:03:50,411
Thank you.

1348
01:03:50,578 --> 01:03:54,331
You're the first person in this process
who's spoken to me like a human.

1349
01:03:59,420 --> 01:04:01,972
You remind me of myself
on my second marriage.

1350
01:04:06,009 --> 01:04:07,971
Come! Come! Come! Come! Oh!

1351
01:04:08,053 --> 01:04:09,635
You have fun with Daddy?

1352
01:04:09,722 --> 01:04:11,844
- We drove around to offices.
- Oh.

1353
01:04:11,932 --> 01:04:14,775
Do you want to see your ninja costume?
It's on G-ma's bed.

1354
01:04:14,852 --> 01:04:16,103
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

1355
01:04:17,980 --> 01:04:20,893
You know, I had Donna build him
this whole Frankenstein thing

1356
01:04:20,983 --> 01:04:22,485
with the plugs and...

1357
01:04:22,568 --> 01:04:25,010
Yeah, well, the cousins are ninjas,
so he wanted to do that...

1358
01:04:25,070 --> 01:04:26,902
But he and I had decided together.

1359
01:04:26,989 --> 01:04:28,671
