Did you dye your hair again?
Is that for your show?

1365
01:04:41,670 --> 01:04:44,302
No, this is me. It was this way
when I saw you before.

1366
01:04:44,381 --> 01:04:46,173
I know, but I didn't say anything then.

1367
01:04:47,342 --> 01:04:48,514
You don't like it?

1368
01:04:48,594 --> 01:04:51,887
No, I guess it's fine.
Is it shorter? I prefer longer but...

1369
01:04:54,725 --> 01:04:56,937
Oh, sorry, it's just absurd.

1370
01:04:57,561 --> 01:04:58,642
Is everything okay?

1371
01:04:58,729 --> 01:05:00,360
Yeah. Why?

1372
01:05:00,856 --> 01:05:03,398
You seem, I don't know,
like something is...

1373
01:05:03,484 --> 01:05:04,615
Everything's fine.

1374
01:05:06,612 --> 01:05:08,323
Okay, I'm going to check in at the hotel,

1375
01:05:08,405 --> 01:05:11,368
but I should be able to get to you guys
by 5:00, 5:30...

1376
01:05:11,450 --> 01:05:13,912
We're going to Cassie's
in Pasadena

1377
01:05:13,994 --> 01:05:15,706
and trick-or-treating with the cousins.

1378
01:05:15,788 --> 01:05:16,949
Cassie lives in Pasadena now?

1379
01:05:17,039 --> 01:05:19,291
Yes. She and Sam moved there
a couple months ago.

1380
01:05:19,374 --> 01:05:20,776
Okay, I don't really know Pasadena.

1381
01:05:20,834 --> 01:05:23,813
- I'll figure it out. What's the address?
- My mom is looking forward to it...

1382
01:05:23,837 --> 01:05:25,839
- I'll text Sam.
- ...and Cassie and Sam are mad.

1383
01:05:25,923 --> 01:05:27,254
- Mad at who?
- You.

1384
01:05:27,340 --> 01:05:29,503
- Cassie and Sam?
- You can understand that.

1385
01:05:29,593 --> 01:05:31,805
So, I think we should probably do
separate Halloweens.

1386
01:05:31,887 --> 01:05:34,409
But if you're okay with it,
then shouldn't they be okay with it?

1387
01:05:34,473 --> 01:05:36,785
- Let's do it this way this time.
- Do you not want me there?

1388
01:05:36,809 --> 01:05:37,680
I'm fine with it.

1389
01:05:37,768 --> 01:05:39,730
- Okay.
- It'll be nice for him.

1390
01:05:39,812 --> 01:05:41,143
He'll have two Halloweens.

1391
01:05:42,064 --> 01:05:45,437
What am I going to do with him for second
Halloween? Walk around Sunset Boulevard?

1392
01:05:45,526 --> 01:05:49,239
Maybe the hotel has something. Or you can
drive to a different neighborhood.

1393
01:05:52,866 --> 01:05:55,779
The sun sets forever.

1394
01:05:57,037 --> 01:05:59,960
There shall never be another dawn.

1395
01:06:01,083 --> 01:06:02,084
No!

1396
01:06:03,669 --> 01:06:05,460
Lady...

1397
01:06:05,963 --> 01:06:08,966
I require the solace of the shadows...

1398
01:06:10,008 --> 01:06:11,349
and the dark!

1399
01:06:30,738 --> 01:06:33,821
Okay, ready for Halloween?

1400
01:06:34,575 --> 01:06:36,286
- Hi.
- Wow, elaborate.

1401
01:06:36,744 --> 01:06:39,305
Sweetheart, don't forget to wear
your jacket. It's getting colder.

1402
01:06:39,329 --> 01:06:41,474
- This is a nice house.
- Ready to go back out?

1403
01:06:41,498 --> 01:06:42,976
- He has to pee.
- No, I don't.

1404
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:44,001
He does.

1405
01:06:44,251 --> 01:06:46,463
Uh, some of his men are in here
and also Bear-Bear.

1406
01:06:46,545 --> 01:06:48,690
You can keep that Bear-Bear,
because I got another one.

1407
01:06:48,714 --> 01:06:50,395
Does he know
that there are two Bear-Bears?

1408
01:06:50,423 --> 01:06:52,926
- It was his idea.
- David Bowie, right? Station to Station?

1409
01:06:53,552 --> 01:06:54,553
Let's Dance.

1410
01:06:55,137 --> 01:06:57,840
Henry, have a great Halloween
with Daddy, okay?

1411
01:06:59,767 --> 01:07:00,768
Have fun.

1412
01:07:04,021 --> 01:07:05,903
Go pee and then we're going back out.

1413
01:07:06,314 --> 01:07:07,876
I'm too tired.

1414
01:07:07,900 --> 01:07:10,442
Go pee, and then
we're going to go drive to Halloween.

1415
01:07:10,861 --> 01:07:12,703
This block looks promising.

1416
01:07:13,488 --> 01:07:14,820
I wish Halloween was over.

1417
01:07:14,907 --> 01:07:16,318
Well, it isn't.

1418
01:07:16,659 --> 01:07:18,991
If we were in New York,
we could be walking.

1419
01:07:19,202 --> 01:07:22,205
But I like that we're sitting right now.
I like to sit.

1420
01:07:22,665 --> 01:07:26,038
That's true, Los Angeles
does have sitting going for it.

1421
01:07:26,418 --> 01:07:29,001
I think that's why
I like Los Angeles better.

1422
01:07:29,087 --> 01:07:30,178
Because you get to sit?

1423
01:07:30,255 --> 01:07:32,377
No, because I like my friends here better.

1424
01:07:32,549 --> 01:07:33,681
That's not true.

1425
01:07:34,384 --> 01:07:36,807
What about Horatio and Poppy?

1426
01:07:36,887 --> 01:07:38,889
Horatio doesn't like me anymore.

1427
01:07:39,347 --> 01:07:40,689
And I don't like Poppy.

1428
01:07:41,141 --> 01:07:42,522
Here, I have Axel.

1429
01:07:42,601 --> 01:07:45,353
Axel's hilarious.
I think you'd like him, Dad.

1430
01:07:46,354 --> 01:07:47,736
And my family's here.

1431
01:07:48,941 --> 01:07:49,942
Besides you.

1432
01:08:18,011 --> 01:08:19,132
Everyone's asleep.

1433
01:09:10,689 --> 01:09:11,690
I need to pee!

1434
01:09:18,405 --> 01:09:19,827
Who gave you a lighter?

1435
01:09:23,076 --> 01:09:24,077
Lift the seat.

1436
01:09:30,333 --> 01:09:32,415
I'm going to have to go back to New York
on Monday.

1437
01:09:32,920 --> 01:09:33,961
Did you flush?

1438
01:09:40,761 --> 01:09:41,762
Wash your hands.

1439
01:09:43,430 --> 01:09:44,972
Will you play with me?

1440
01:09:45,974 --> 01:09:47,475
I'm tired, honey.

1441
01:09:59,863 --> 01:10:01,945
Did you hear me?
I have to go back to New York.

1442
01:10:02,032 --> 01:10:04,164
Ah, watch out!
Whoosh! I'm falling!

1443
01:10:06,661 --> 01:10:09,494
You didn't catch me.

1444
01:10:12,417 --> 01:10:13,418
Okay?

1445
01:10:14,252 --> 01:10:15,503
Why aren't you here more?

1446
01:10:17,089 --> 01:10:19,041
I have to work.

1447
01:10:19,382 --> 01:10:21,384
You know my play is opening on Broadway.

1448
01:10:22,094 --> 01:10:24,046
Is it because you don't want to be
near Mom?

1449
01:10:24,137 --> 01:10:26,219
No. You know,
like we talked about,

1450
01:10:26,306 --> 01:10:28,859
we both decided not to be together
no matter where we are,

1451
01:10:28,934 --> 01:10:30,555
but we both want to be with you.

1452
01:10:31,394 --> 01:10:33,767
But you're not near me
if you're in New York.

1453
01:10:34,314 --> 01:10:36,156
Well, we all still live in New York.

1454
01:10:36,817 --> 01:10:38,658
Yeah, but I go to school here.

1455
01:10:39,319 --> 01:10:40,370
Just for right now.

1456
01:10:41,279 --> 01:10:43,661
Like that time we were in Copenhagen
for my play.

1457
01:10:43,740 --> 01:10:46,163
Remember all those kids in buckets?

1458
01:10:46,243 --> 01:10:47,414
I like my school here,

1459
01:10:47,494 --> 01:10:50,037
and Mom says we could stay here
if we want.

1460
01:10:51,957 --> 01:10:52,958
What do you mean?

1461
01:10:55,002 --> 01:10:56,003
She said that?

1462
01:10:56,253 --> 01:10:57,254
Yeah.

1463
01:11:03,760 --> 01:11:04,932
Vroom.

1464
01:11:06,972 --> 01:11:07,973
Aah!

1465
01:11:24,781 --> 01:11:27,324
- Hello?
- Are you moving out here?

1466
01:11:28,410 --> 01:11:31,180
- Did you find a lawyer?
- Yes. Henry says you're moving here.

1467
01:11:31,204 --> 01:11:32,455
Have your lawyer call Nora.

1468
01:11:32,539 --> 01:11:33,871
I want to talk about it as us.

1469
01:11:33,957 --> 01:11:34,958
