like to do together?

2274
01:50:50,853 --> 01:50:53,436
When I'm at my dad's,
we sometimes watch a movie,

2275
01:50:53,523 --> 01:50:55,144
or build a Lego, or something.

2276
01:50:55,941 --> 01:50:57,783
My dad's a great Lego builder.

2277
01:50:58,194 --> 01:50:59,535
And at your mom's?

2278
01:51:00,280 --> 01:51:03,783
At home, I have most of my toys,
and there's a pool,

2279
01:51:04,284 --> 01:51:06,326
and I have a tree house and jungle gym.

2280
01:51:08,037 --> 01:51:11,451
We have super secret treasure hunt,
which is really fun.

2281
01:51:12,875 --> 01:51:16,379
- Sweetheart?
- Army men ride in here and...

2282
01:51:16,462 --> 01:51:18,093
Want to help me set the table?

2283
01:51:18,673 --> 01:51:19,594
Do I have to?

2284
01:51:19,674 --> 01:51:22,257
- Just come in here and grab a plate.
- I'm playing.

2285
01:51:22,343 --> 01:51:23,344
Henry?

2286
01:51:24,262 --> 01:51:25,643
Okay.

2287
01:51:26,556 --> 01:51:27,557
Fine.

2288
01:51:31,644 --> 01:51:33,476
- Why are you being like this?
- What?

2289
01:51:33,563 --> 01:51:35,435
If I ask you to help out, help out.

2290
01:51:35,523 --> 01:51:37,695
- What is this?
- Special Meal.

2291
01:51:38,526 --> 01:51:39,907
What are the green things?

2292
01:51:40,486 --> 01:51:42,578
There aren't green things in Special Meal.

2293
01:51:42,655 --> 01:51:44,947
- It's just a garnish.
- Ugh.

2294
01:51:45,032 --> 01:51:46,033
I'll take it off.

2295
01:51:47,076 --> 01:51:49,078
I don't want to eat anything it touched.

2296
01:51:49,161 --> 01:51:52,875
- It doesn't change the taste of anything.
- I might want to be a vegetarian.

2297
01:51:53,499 --> 01:51:54,670
Mom's a vegetarian.

2298
01:51:54,750 --> 01:51:56,131
Is she a vegetarian now?

2299
01:51:56,711 --> 01:51:58,513
- Yeah.
- Well, then, you should like garnish.

2300
01:51:58,588 --> 01:52:00,460
It's all garnish, vegetarianism.

2301
01:52:02,508 --> 01:52:03,929
I'm done with my water.

2302
01:52:13,978 --> 01:52:15,270
Sure I can't get you anything?

2303
01:52:15,355 --> 01:52:17,056
No, I'm fine, thank you.

2304
01:52:19,692 --> 01:52:21,063
Do the thing with the knife.

2305
01:52:21,151 --> 01:52:22,983
No, I'm not.

2306
01:52:23,946 --> 01:52:24,947
No.

2307
01:52:25,740 --> 01:52:26,741
Come on.

2308
01:52:26,991 --> 01:52:28,202
It's not a dinner thing.

2309
01:52:31,245 --> 01:52:32,707
It's not an any time thing.

2310
01:52:33,205 --> 01:52:34,877
What's the thing with the knife?

2311
01:52:35,708 --> 01:52:36,879
It's hilarious.

2312
01:52:36,959 --> 01:52:39,422
No, it's dumb.
I have a small knife on my keychain,

2313
01:52:39,504 --> 01:52:40,755
which is only for adults.

2314
01:52:42,465 --> 01:52:44,216
And I do a thing with it sometimes.

2315
01:52:45,718 --> 01:52:47,300
You said I could get a knife.

2316
01:52:47,803 --> 01:52:49,685
A jackknife, yeah, when you're older.

2317
01:52:50,390 --> 01:52:51,391
Like ten.

2318
01:52:51,849 --> 01:52:53,271
No, like 20.

2319
01:52:53,934 --> 01:52:54,935
Yeah.

2320
01:53:00,274 --> 01:53:04,529
Dime, rime, lime, pime, sime...

2321
01:53:04,612 --> 01:53:06,654
Honey, stop guessing.
You're so close. Stay with it.

2322
01:53:06,697 --> 01:53:08,819
Ugh, I don't want to do it.

2323
01:53:08,991 --> 01:53:12,495
- What's the first letter?
- I don't want to do it. Can I do the iPad?

2324
01:53:12,578 --> 01:53:14,039
No, look. What's the first letter?

2325
01:53:14,414 --> 01:53:16,576
- I don't want to.
- It's a T. What sound does T make?

2326
01:53:16,666 --> 01:53:18,998
- Tuh.
- Right. Then just do the rest of it.

2327
01:53:19,585 --> 01:53:20,586
Dime.

2328
01:53:21,462 --> 01:53:22,333
No.

2329
01:53:22,422 --> 01:53:24,714
You have "tuh" and "ime." What is that?

2330
01:53:27,843 --> 01:53:28,844
Time.

2331
01:53:29,387 --> 01:53:30,388
It's time.

2332
01:53:31,639 --> 01:53:32,640
It's time.

2333
01:53:37,687 --> 01:53:38,688
You'll see, honey.

2334
01:53:38,771 --> 01:53:41,814
One day, it's just going to click
and you'll be able to read everything.

2335
01:53:42,650 --> 01:53:43,861
I need a break.

2336
01:53:44,276 --> 01:53:46,068
Can I go play in my room?

2337
01:53:46,153 --> 01:53:47,154
Sure.

2338
01:53:49,407 --> 01:53:50,408
Hey.

2339
01:53:52,577 --> 01:53:53,578
Yeah?

2340
01:54:10,970 --> 01:54:12,762
Do you ever observe married people?

2341
01:54:12,847 --> 01:54:14,018
No. Why would I?

2342
01:54:14,849 --> 01:54:16,641
- I was kidding.
- Oh.

2343
01:54:28,028 --> 01:54:31,361
The knife thing is...
I carry this knife on my keychain,

2344
01:54:31,449 --> 01:54:33,160
which his mother got me, actually.

2345
01:54:34,869 --> 01:54:37,371
And I do this thing for his mom
where I pretend to cut myself,

2346
01:54:37,455 --> 01:54:40,127
but I retract the blade,
but I-I don't do it with him.

2347
01:54:43,419 --> 01:54:44,760
Oh.

2348
01:54:45,630 --> 01:54:47,171
- That's fine.
- Are you okay?

2349
01:54:47,256 --> 01:54:49,629
Yeah, I must not have retracted
the blade all the way.

2350
01:54:49,717 --> 01:54:51,178
- Do you need...
- Yeah.

2351
01:54:52,595 --> 01:54:54,767
Yeah, no, it's fine.

2352
01:54:55,180 --> 01:54:56,432
What else can I tell you?

2353
01:54:57,307 --> 01:55:00,310
- Um, I think I have enough.
- You have enough?

2354
01:55:00,811 --> 01:55:03,393
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Totally. I'm fine.

2355
01:55:04,023 --> 01:55:06,936
Uh, well, I'll leave you guys for tonight.

2356
01:55:07,527 --> 01:55:08,528
Oh, okay.

2357
01:55:09,403 --> 01:55:12,487
I'll be in touch
if I have further questions.

2358
01:55:13,574 --> 01:55:15,075
Uh... Oh, thanks.

2359
01:55:15,159 --> 01:55:16,160
Um...

2360
01:55:17,244 --> 01:55:18,876
Oh, thanks. Um...

2361
01:55:21,415 --> 01:55:23,628
Thanks. Thank you for the water.

2362
01:55:23,709 --> 01:55:26,251
- Oh, yeah, sure.
- Are you sure you're okay?

2363
01:55:26,336 --> 01:55:27,708
- Yeah.
- Okay.

2364
01:55:28,673 --> 01:55:29,884
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

2365
01:55:34,845 --> 01:55:36,256
Oh. Sorry.

2366
01:55:37,682 --> 01:55:38,683
All right, let...

2367
01:55:41,477 --> 01:55:42,818
I think you turn the...

2368
01:55:46,566 --> 01:55:47,897
- Okay.
- Sorry.

2369
01:55:48,400 --> 01:55:49,401
Okay.

2370
01:56:52,965 --> 01:56:54,296
Dad, are you okay?

2371
01:56:55,009 --> 01:56:56,390
Yeah, I'm just tired.

2372
01:57:13,611 --> 01:57:15,162
Dad, did she like us?

2373
01:57:17,239 --> 01:57:19,662
Yeah, she thought we were great.

2374
01:58:53,127 --> 01:58:54,168
Guys, slow down.

2375
01:58:55,838 --> 01:58:56,839
So...

2376
01:58:57,006 --> 01:58:59,378
because Charlie dropped his claim
to New York,

2377
01:58:59,466 --> 01:59:00,517
we're mostly done.

2378
01:59:00,801 --> 01:59:02,092
Jay's lost interest,

2379
01:59:02,261 --> 01:59:04,593
and Ted, his associate,
is doing the paperwork.

2380
01:59:04,680 --> 01:59:06,431
And we're not taking any money, right?

2381
01:59:06,515 --> 01:59:08,718
We withdrew our claim for the MacArthur,

2382
01:59:08,809 --> 01:59:10,971
which I think
we could have gotten, by the way,

2383
01:59:11,061 --> 01:59:13,313
and they're not asking
for any of the show.

2384
01:59:14,439 --> 01:59:16,031
Thank you for everything, Nora.

2385
01:59:16,358 --> 01:59:17,780
You're welcome, doll.

2386
01:59:18,527 --> 01:59:20,279
To your new home in LA.

2387
01:59:24,074 --> 01:59:25,075
Mmm.

2388
01:59:25,409 --> 01:59:26,410
And...

2389
01:59:26,576 --> 01:59:27,948
whenever Charlie is in LA,

2390
01:59:28,037 --> 01:59:31,080
I got the custody breakdown to be 55/45.

2391
01:59:31,540 --> 01:59:34,453
So you'll have Henry an extra day
every two weeks.

2392
01:59:34,877 --> 01:59:36,248
I thought we made it equal.

2393
01:59:36,420 --> 01:59:38,092
I tweaked it at the last minute.

2394
01:59:38,172 --> 01:59:41,005
I just didn't want him
to be able to say he got 50/50,

2395
01:59:41,091 --> 01:59:42,552
bragging to his friends.

2396
01:59:43,052 --> 01:59:45,094
- But I don't want to do that.
- Take it.

2397
01:59:45,554 --> 01:59:46,595
You won.

2398
01:59:48,223 --> 01:59:49,224
Uh-huh.

2399
02:00:13,040 --> 02:00:15,292
Hi. You look like a guy
who really cares about animals.

2400
02:00:15,375 --> 02:00:16,376
Nope.

2401
02:00:36,146 --> 02:00:37,938
Oh, my God!

2402
02:00:38,190 --> 02:00:39,191
Hi.

2403
02:00:54,498 --> 02:00:56,881
The couch was technically hers,
pre-marriage.

2404
02:00:56,959 --> 02:00:58,881
But I mean... it was our couch.

2405
02:00:58,961 --> 02:01:00,803
It's not like I was going to buy
another couch.

2406
02:01:00,838 --> 02:01:03,240
But then when it comes time to split,
it's suddenly her couch

2407
02:01:03,298 --> 02:01:04,679
and I have no couch, and...

2408
02:01:05,384 --> 02:01:06,675
Hey, guys, what's up?

2409
02:01:07,552 --> 02:01:09,805
I'm sitting on the floor
is the short version.

2410
02:01:12,432 --> 02:01:15,185
I'm sorry.
This is all so self-pitying and boring.

2411
02:01:15,269 --> 02:01:16,270
No, come on.

2412
02:01:16,353 --> 02:01:18,105
No, it's so stupid. I'm sorry.

2413
02:01:18,188 --> 02:01:21,021
- It sounds really tough.
- No, no, no, no. It is sad.

2414
02:01:40,419 --> 02:01:42,461
It's true, but there's more than that.

2415
02:01:42,671 --> 02:01:44,423
Is that all you think there is to it?

2416
02:01:44,506 --> 02:01:46,869
You have so many reasons
for not being with someone, Robert,

2417
02:01:46,926 --> 02:01:48,968
but you haven't got one good reason
for being alone.

2418
02:01:49,011 --> 02:01:51,513
C'mon, you're onto something.
Robbie, you're onto something.

2419
02:02:03,859 --> 02:02:07,322
You see what you look for, you know?
You're not a kid anymore, Robbie.

2420
02:02:07,404 --> 02:02:09,536
I don't think you'll ever be
a kid again, kiddo.

2421
02:02:21,543 --> 02:02:24,877
Blow out the candles, Robert,
and make a wish.

2422
02:02:24,964 --> 02:02:26,295
Want something.

2423
02:02:27,091 --> 02:02:28,422
Want something.

2424
02:04:41,850 --> 02:04:43,052
Hello?

2425
02:04:52,902 --> 02:04:54,234
Hello?

2426
02:04:55,905 --> 02:04:58,028
- Hi. Sorry, the door was open.
- Shh.

2427
02:04:58,992 --> 02:05:00,034
Oh, okay.

2428
02:05:02,287 --> 02:05:03,498
Whoa! Gotcha!

2429
02:05:03,580 --> 02:05:04,581
Aah!

2430
02:05:04,998 --> 02:05:06,500
Oh, Charlie!

2431
02:05:07,084 --> 02:05:09,586
Oh! Was your flight okay?

2432
02:05:09,669 --> 02:05:11,131
- Yeah.
- Carter.

2433
02:05:11,213 --> 02:05:12,294
Charlie.

2434
02:05:12,381 --> 02:05:13,542
Nicole's still at work.

2435
02:05:21,098 --> 02:05:22,349
- Hi.
- Hi.

2436
02:05:22,432 --> 02:05:23,433
Can I get a hug?

2437
02:05:28,688 --> 02:05:30,100
- Hey, how'd it go?
- Hey.

2438
02:05:30,190 --> 02:05:33,253
Good, yeah. Donny's dead now. We shot
the scene where he merges with the ficus.

2439
02:05:33,277 --> 02:05:35,560
- Henry's upstairs.
- She got an Emmy nomination.

2440
02:05:35,779 --> 02:05:38,242
- She's a great actress.
- No, for directing.

2441
02:05:39,908 --> 02:05:41,740
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

2442
02:05:41,826 --> 02:05:44,579
Now I know what you were
so obsessed with all the time.

2443
02:05:44,663 --> 02:05:46,575
- Um, we should get ready.
- Yeah.

2444
02:05:46,665 --> 02:05:48,559
- We're the Beatles.
- Come on, Charlie.

2445
02:05:48,583 --> 02:05:50,145
I didn't really get a costume together.

2446
02:05:50,169 --> 02:05:52,438
- You could be George Martin.
- I don't need to be anything.

2447
02:05:52,462 --> 02:05:54,815
- You've got to be something.
- A ghost. I'll get you a sheet.

2448
02:05:54,839 --> 02:05:56,984
I have the album cover
if anyone needs to reference it.

2449
02:05:57,008 --> 02:05:59,881
And we should leave soon. I'm saying that
as much for me as anyone else.

2450
02:05:59,969 --> 02:06:02,532
- Am I John or George?
- Trick-or-treating starts at 5:00.

2451
02:06:02,556 --> 02:06:04,117
You're George. Nicole is John.

2452
02:06:10,980 --> 02:06:13,853
I wanted to tell you
I took a residency at UCLA.

2453
02:06:15,485 --> 02:06:17,947
I'm going to direct two plays
in rep at REDCAT.

2454
02:06:19,989 --> 02:06:20,990
Oh.

2455
02:06:21,783 --> 02:06:23,325
So, I'm going to be here for a while.

2456
02:06:26,538 --> 02:06:27,539
That's great.

2457
02:06:30,709 --> 02:06:31,710
Are you okay?

2458
